		<div class="postbody">
			

			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p17791" rel="nofollow"><!-- google_ad_section_start -->Pick The Year This Deal Becomes A Bad Contract<!-- google_ad_section_end --></a></h3>
			<p class="author"><!-- google_ad_section_start(weight=ignore) --><a rel="nofollow" href="./viewtopic.php?p=17791&amp;sid=e4217d8a8df5d8a2ba82218c898d18f6#p17791"><img src="./styles/static/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>Post <a href="./viewtopic.php?p=17791&amp;sid=e4217d8a8df5d8a2ba82218c898d18f6#p17791" onclick="prompt('Direct link to post:',this.href); return false;"><strong>#1</strong></a>&nbsp;by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=179&amp;sid=e4217d8a8df5d8a2ba82218c898d18f6" style="color: #000000;" class="username-coloured">ofahn</a></strong> &raquo; December 25th, 2012, 11:39 am <!-- google_ad_section_end --></p>

			

			<div id="explanation17791" style="display:none" >
					<form action="" method="post">
						<fieldset>
							<textarea name="comment_text" cols="60" rows="5"></textarea><br />
							<input name="comment_to_id" type="hidden" value="179" />
							<input name="Submit" type="submit" class="button1" value="Submit" />
						</fieldset>
					</form>
			</div>



			<div class="content"><!-- google_ad_section_start -->This winter teams have made a series of long term commitments (multi year contracts and extensions) to players that are probably on the downside of their careers.  It's extremely rare that these deals do not have at least ONE bad contract year.  Sometimes it's because they are back loaded and the bulk of the money is scheduled to be paid during the least productive years, and sometimes because the contract <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-style: italic">at least</span></span> one year beyond the player's ability to produce at the level he was given the contract for.<br /><br />Some contracts like Álex Rodríguez's 10/275M in 2007, Milton Bradley's 3/31M in 2009, Oliver Perez's 3/36M the same year, and Jason Werth's the next year you just KNOW are mistakes before the ink dries.  Others like Mark Texiera's 8/180M signed in 2009 LOOKED like they might not be too long, but it's beginning to appear like at least some of the end years will be a bad contract.<br /><br />Even the rare long term free agent contract that was on track to be solid through its entire length can be ruined by an extension.  Does anyone REALLY believe the 5/122M extension the Yankees gave to CC Sabathia in 2011 will be a good contract until the end?<br /><br />Most &quot;free&quot; agent contracts of three years or more become a liability at some point to the signing team.  In a different post I'll explain why I consider the Orioles one of the 2012/13 off season winners because they weren't stupid enough to give in to the ABSURD demands of Josh Hamilton, Zack Greinke, Edwin Jackson, Nick Swisher, Shane Victorino, Anibel Sanchez, or Johnny Gomes.<br /><br />Some teams have the payroll room to take a big risk on the out years of a bad contract for a player they believe they need RIGHT NOW.  A perfect example is the Los Angeles Dodgers who now have more bad contracts than Hollywood has bad face lifts.<br /><br />Here's a list of some of the most questionable contracts of the last two years.  Which contracts do you believe will have bad contract years and when?  Please explain <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">WHY</span></span> you feels that way.  I'll post my own opinions tomorrow.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;">2012</span></span><br /><br />Joe Blanton 	SP 	Angels 	No 	2 	$15.000MM<br />Jonathan Broxton 	RP	Reds  	3 	$21.000MM<br />Melky Cabrera 	LF 	Blue Jays 	No 	2 	$16.000MM<br />Ryan Dempster 	SP 	Red Sox  	2 	$26.500MM<br />R.A. Dickey 	SP 	Mets 	No 	3 	$29.000MM (ext)<br />Jonny Gomes 	LF 	Red Sox 	No 	2 	$10.000MM<br />Zack Greinke 	SP 	Dodgers 	No 	6 	$147.000MM<br />Jeremy Guthrie 	SP 	Royals  	3 	$25.000MM<br />Josh Hamilton 	LF / CF 	Angels 	5 	$125.000MM<br />Torii Hunter 	RF 	Tigers 	No 	2 	$26.000MM<br />Edwin Jackson 	SP 	Cubs  	4 	$52.000MM<br />Brandon League 	RP  	Dodgers  	3 	$22.500MM<br />Francisco Liriano 	SP 	Pirates 	2 	$12.750MM<br />Ryan Ludwick 	LF 	Reds 	2 	$15.000MM<br />Russell Martin 	C 	Pirates  	2 	$17.000MM<br />Brandon McCarthy 	SP 	Diamondbacks 	2 	$15.500MM<br />Mike Napoli 	1B / C 	Red Sox  	3 	$39.000MM<br />David Ortiz 	DH 	Red Sox 	 	2 	$26.000MM<br />Angel Pagan 	CF 	Giants 	No 	4 	$40.000MM<br />Jake Peavy 	SP 	White Sox  	2 	$29.000MM<br />Cody Ross 	OF 	Diamondbacks	3 	$26.000MM<br />Anibal Sanchez 	SP 	Tigers  	5 	$80.000MM<br />Marco Scutaro 	IF 	Giants 	        3 	$20.000MM<br />Joakim Soria 	RP  	Rangers 	 	2 	$8.000MM<br />Nick Swisher 	1B / RF 	Indians  	4 	$56.000MM<br />B.J. Upton 	CF 	Braves 	 	5 	$75.000MM<br />Shane Victorino 	OF 	Red Sox  	3 	$39.000MM<br />David Wright 	3B 	Mets 	 	8      $127.000MM (ext)<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;">2011</span></span><br /><br />Clint Barmes 	2B / SS 	Pirates 	 	2 	$10.500MM<br />Heath Bell 	RP 	Marlins 	 	3 	$27.000MM<br />Carlos Beltran 	RF 	Cardinals 	 	2 	$26.000MM<br />Mark Buehrle 	SP 	Marlins 	 	4 	$58.000MM<br />Yoenis Cespedes 	OF 	Athletics 		4 	$36.000MM<br />Wei-Yin Chen 	SP 	Orioles 		3 	$11.388MM<br />Coco Crisp 	CF 	Athletics 		2 	$14.000MM<br />Chris Capuano 	SP 	Dodgers 		2 	$10.000MM<br />David DeJesus 	OF 	Cubs 	 	2 	$10.000MM<br />Mark Ellis 	2B 	Dodgers 	 	2 	$8.750MM<br />Prince Fielder 	1B 	Tigers 	 	9 	$214.000MM<br />Frank Francisco 	RP  	Mets 	 	2 	$12.000MM<br />Aaron Harang 	SP 	Dodgers 	 	2 	$12.000MM<br />Aaron Hill 	2B 	Diamondbacks 	 	2 	$11.000MM<br />Jonathan Papelbon 	RP 	Phillies 	 	4 	$50.000MM<br />Albert Pujols 	1B 	Angels 	 	10 	$246.842MM<br />Jose Reyes 	SS 	Marlins 	 	6 	$106.000MM<br />Jimmy Rollins 	SS 	Phillies 	 	3 	$38.000MM<br />CC Sabathia 	SP 	Yankees 	 	5 	$122.000MM (ext)<br />C.J. Wilson 	SP 	Angels 	 	5 	$77.500MM<!-- google_ad_section_end --></div>
						

