			<div class="content"><!-- google_ad_section_start -->IMO the WORST contracts and extensions of the last two years are (in no particular order):<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;">2012</span></span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Zack Greinke</span> SP Dodgers 6 $147.000MM  the Dodgers just brought a pitcher that has had issues with pressure into what may be the biggest expectations in baseball in 2013.  What could go wrong?  If LA gets even three good years out of this deal they should feel lucky.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Josh Hamilton</span> LF / CF Angels 5 $125.000MM  let's see - substance abuse problems with recent relapses.  A body that's starting to breakdown and some legitimate questions about his desire to perform at a plus level anymore.  OF COURSE the Angels had good reason to not require a behavior or injury clause.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Edwin Jackson </span>SP Cubs 4 $52.000MM  a &quot;can't miss&quot; prospect that has played for EIGHT ML teams by the time he's 28.  No <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="color: #FF0000">RED FLAGS</span></span> there.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Brandon League</span> RP Dodgers 3 $22.500MM  ONE decent year as a closer in a no pressure situation in Seattle <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">does not mean</span></span> that he'll be ready to close for a team that will be under &quot;must win&quot; pressure.  Last year his WHIP exploded in Seattle and they traded him just in time.  I hope the Dodgers intention was to simply pay for sh#ts and giggles three times the going rate for a middle reliever so they won't be disappointed by (at least) the last two years of this contract.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Russell Martin</span> C Pirates 2 $17.000MM  maybe the Pirates think that his performance will improve in a non pressure situation like Pittsburgh.  I wonder if the Pirates even considered the fact that he may not have the best catching skills to be a mentor for their young pitching prospects.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Mike Napoli</span> 1B / C Red Sox 3 $39.000MM  if this contract is finally completed as it was agreed to it you'll probably be able to time with a stop watch when it will become a bad contract.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Angel Pagan</span> CF Giants No 4 $40.000MM  WTF?!?!?!  Did the Giants become nostalgic for a Juan Pierre disaster of a contract?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Cody Ross</span> OF Diamondbacks 3 $26.000MM  he's been so inconsistent over his career that at least one of these contract years will be bad.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Anibal Sanchez</span> SP Tigers 5 $80.000MM  the Tigers are all in for 2013 so they over paid by about 3M a year and about two contract years.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Marco Scutaro</span> IF Giants 3 $20.000MM  WOW!  There's nothing that screams bad contract like paying a 39 YO middle IF 7M.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Nick Swisher</span> 1B / RF Indians 4 $56.000MM  a good player but Cleveland was so desperate to land one that they were probably bidding against themselves and went about two bad contract years too far.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">B.J. Upton</span> CF Braves 5 $75.000MM  this contract all depends on which B J Upton shows up.  The one that's indifferent and doesn't hustle or the one that plays like an All Star.  The Braves better hope it's the latter or they're going to be counting pennies trying to pay for someone to cover for him through 2017.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Shane Victorino</span> OF Red Sox 3 $39.000MM  OMG!!!  WTF?!?!  WOW!  Let me catch my breath...I mean OMG!!!  WTF?!?!<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">David Wright</span> 3B Mets 8 $127.000MM (ext)  with Wright's back history only the Mets' orthopedist can realistically guess how many bad contract years are in this boondoggle.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="font-size: 150%; line-height: 116%;">2011</span></span><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Clint Barmes</span> 2B / SS Pirates 2 $10.500MM  was anyone really surprised that his <a href="http://orioles-nation.com/library/ops-plus/" class="autolink postlink-local">OPS</a> fell off the table at age 33?  Just imagine what his age 34 contract year will bring.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Heath Bell</span> RP Marlins 3 $27.000MM  who would have guessed that taking a 34 YO closer away from the only situation that had ever been successful in would be a bad idea?  Not the Marlins who are paying the Diamondbacks 8M to have Bell pitch for them.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Mark Buehrle</span> SP Marlins 4 $58.000MM  this one will probably be like the Derek Lowe 4/60M Atlanta deal. One bad contract year too long.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Prince Fielder</span> 1B Tigers 9 $214.000MM  there's nothing wrong with this contract unless you have a problem with paying Fat Albert to waddle up to the plate as your DH for about the last three or four years of the deal.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Frank Francisco</span> RP Mets 2 $12.000MM  the signs of decline were all there but the Mets just couldn't help themselves.  Maybe they missed the Oliver Perez drama.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Jonathan Papelbon</span> RP Phillies 4 $50.000MM  &quot;Danger, there's a breakdown dead ahead&quot; - Boz Scaggs saw this one coming back in the mid 70s.  <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MgsUdk8TgdM" rel="nofollow" onclick="this.target='_blank';">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=MgsUdk8TgdM</a><!-- m --><br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Albert Pujols</span> 1B Angels 10 $246.842MM  the Angels decided to bring Albert to Los Angeles because they were concerned Hollywood wouldn't have enough broken down, overpaid has beens in about five years.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Jose Reyes</span> SS Marlins 6 $106.000MM  a history of injuries and a realistic lost of speed won't make the last few years of this contract bad, will it?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">Jimmy Rollins</span> SS Phillies 3 $38.000MM  giving three more years to a 32 YO SS who had been in decline over the last few years isn't a bad idea, is it?<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">CC Sabathia</span> SP Yankees 5 $122.000MM (ext)  the great unanswered question is NOT what's the meaning of life but, rather whether the last two <span style="font-weight: bold"><span style="text-decoration: underline">OR</span></span> three years of this deal will be a bad contract.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold">C.J. Wilson</span> SP Angels 5 $77.500MM  apparently, the Angels never heard of John Lackey or A J Burnett.<!-- google_ad_section_end --></div>
						

